PortfolioPilot / DiversifyAI - API Infrastructure (Current Implementation)

Base URL
- Default: http://localhost:5000/api
- Frontend reads from VITE_API_BASE_URL and falls back to http://localhost:5000/api.

Authentication and Authorization
- JWT Bearer token is required for protected routes.
- Header format: Authorization: Bearer <token>
- Roles in system: client, advisor, admin
- Role checks:
	- Admin-only: creating advisor accounts
	- Advisor-only: earnings dashboard, advisor room list
	- Client-only: client consultation history

Session and Payment Rules
- Consultation access window: 24 hours after successful payment verification.
- Clients need an active paid session to create/send chat messages.
- Advisors can access chat without payment middleware checks.
- Users can still read historical chat messages after expiry if they are chat participants.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1) Health API
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

GET /api/health
- Auth: Public
- Purpose: Basic API liveness check.
- Response:
	{
		"status": "API running"
	}

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
2) Auth APIs
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

POST /api/auth/register
- Auth: Public
- Purpose: Register a new client account (public signup is client-only).
- Body:
	{
		"name": "Madhav Gill",
		"email": "madhav@gmail.com",
		"password": "123456"
	}
- Behavior:
	- Rejects missing fields.
	- Rejects duplicate email.
	- Rejects configured admin email for public signup.
	- Creates user with role = client.
- Response:
	{
		"token": "jwt_token",
		"user": {
			"id": "...",
			"name": "Madhav Gill",
			"email": "madhav@gmail.com",
			"role": "client"
		}
	}

POST /api/auth/login
- Auth: Public
- Purpose: Login for client/advisor/admin.
- Body:
	{
		"email": "madhav@gmail.com",
		"password": "123456"
	}
- Behavior:
	- For configured ADMIN_EMAIL + ADMIN_PASSWORD, returns admin session.
	- Auto-creates admin user record if missing.
	- Ensures admin role on existing admin user.
	- For normal users, validates hashed password.
- Response:
	{
		"token": "jwt_token",
		"user": {
			"id": "...",
			"name": "...",
			"email": "...",
			"role": "client|advisor|admin"
		}
	}

GET /api/auth/advisors
- Auth: Public
- Purpose: List advisor users for advisor discovery pages.
- Response:
	{
		"advisors": [
			{
				"_id": "...",
				"name": "Advisor Name",
				"email": "advisor@example.com",
				"createdAt": "..."
			}
		]
	}

POST /api/auth/admin/create-advisor
- Auth: Protected + admin role required
- Purpose: Admin-only onboarding of advisor accounts.
- Body:
	{
		"name": "Advisor Name",
		"email": "advisor@example.com",
		"password": "strongpass"
	}
- Behavior:
	- Only configured platform admin can call successfully.
	- Rejects missing fields, duplicate email, weak password, admin email reuse.
	- Creates user with role = advisor.
- Response:
	{
		"message": "Advisor account created successfully",
		"advisor": {
			"id": "...",
			"name": "Advisor Name",
			"email": "advisor@example.com",
			"role": "advisor"
		}
	}

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3) Portfolio APIs
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

GET /api/portfolio/search?q=<query>
- Auth: Protected
- Purpose: Search Indian stocks through Yahoo Finance.
- Behavior:
	- Filters NSE/BSE symbols.
	- Normalizes symbol display and includes basic metadata.
- Response (array):
	[
		{
			"symbol": "RELIANCE",
			"name": "Reliance Industries",
			"fullSymbol": "RELIANCE.NS",
			"type": "EQUITY",
			"sector": "Energy"
		}
	]

GET /api/portfolio
- Auth: Protected
- Purpose: Return user portfolio summary + holdings.
- Query params:
	- forceRefresh=true (optional): forces live price refresh now.
- Behavior:
	- Refreshes live prices at most once per 24h by default.
	- Stores and returns pricesLastUpdatedAt.
	- Returns empty-safe payload for users with no holdings.
- Response:
	{
		"totalInvestment": 25000,
		"totalStocks": 3,
		"stocks": [
			{
				"symbol": "RELIANCE",
				"quantity": 10,
				"sector": "Energy",
				"currentValue": 12000,
				"buyPrice": 2500
			}
		],
		"pricesLastUpdatedAt": "2026-03-19T00:00:00.000Z"
	}

POST /api/portfolio/add
- Auth: Protected
- Purpose: Add a holding to the portfolio.
- Body:
	{
		"stockSymbol": "RELIANCE",
		"quantity": 10,
		"buyPrice": 2500,
		"sector": "Energy"
	}
- Behavior:
	- Requires stockSymbol, quantity, buyPrice.
	- Attempts Yahoo quote for live pricing and sector enrichment.
	- Appends new stock entry (no merge/upsert logic).
- Response:
	{
		"message": "Stock added",
		"stock": {
			"symbol": "RELIANCE",
			"quantity": 10,
			"buyPrice": 2500,
			"sector": "Energy",
			"currentValue": 25100
		}
	}

DELETE /api/portfolio/remove/:symbol
- Auth: Protected
- Purpose: Remove a holding by symbol.
- Behavior:
	- Symbol comparison is uppercase.
	- Updates pricesLastUpdatedAt.
- Response:
	{
		"message": "Stock removed successfully"
	}

GET /api/portfolio/sectors
- Auth: Protected
- Purpose: Return sector allocation percentages.
- Behavior:
	- Uses currentValue if present, else buyPrice * quantity.
	- Rounds percentages and sorts descending by allocation.
- Response:
	{
		"Banking": 35,
		"IT": 25,
		"Energy": 20,
		"Pharma": 10,
		"FMCG": 10
	}

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
4) Analysis APIs
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

POST /api/analysis/portfolio
- Auth: Protected
- Purpose: Generate AI portfolio analysis (or return daily cached result).
- Behavior:
	- One snapshot per user per UTC day (cache first).
	- If portfolio empty: returns zero scores and guidance text.
	- Uses MegaLLM OpenAI-compatible endpoint.
	- Persists snapshot with generatedAt and isCached marker.
- Response:
	{
		"diversificationScore": 68,
		"riskScore": 55,
		"portfolioHealth": 72,
		"marketCapMix": {
			"Large Cap": 60,
			"Mid Cap": 25,
			"Small Cap": 15
		},
		"recommendations": ["..."],
		"generatedAt": "...",
		"isCached": false
	}

GET /api/analysis/latest
- Auth: Protected
- Purpose: Fetch latest stored analysis without invoking LLM.
- Behavior:
	- Returns zeroed safe response if no snapshot exists.
	- Always marks response as cached.
- Response:
	{
		"diversificationScore": 68,
		"riskScore": 55,
		"portfolioHealth": 72,
		"marketCapMix": {
			"Large Cap": 60,
			"Mid Cap": 25,
			"Small Cap": 15
		},
		"recommendations": ["..."],
		"generatedAt": "...",
		"isCached": true
	}

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
5) Payment APIs
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

POST /api/payment/create-order
- Auth: Protected
- Purpose: Create Razorpay order for advisor consultation.
- Body:
	{
		"amount": 499,
		"advisorId": "<advisorObjectId>"
	}
- Behavior:
	- Validates amount > 0 and advisorId format.
	- Creates local Payment record with status = created.
- Response:
	{
		"message": "Order created successfully",
		"order": {
			"id": "order_xxx",
			"amount": 49900,
			"currency": "INR",
			"receipt": "receipt_xxx"
		},
		"paymentId": "<paymentObjectId>"
	}

POST /api/payment/verify
- Auth: Protected
- Purpose: Verify Razorpay signature and unlock consultation session.
- Body:
	{
		"razorpay_order_id": "order_xxx",
		"razorpay_payment_id": "pay_xxx",
		"razorpay_signature": "signature_xxx",
		"advisorId": "<advisorObjectId>"
	}
- Behavior:
	- Verifies signature.
	- On success:
		- updates payment status to paid
		- sets paidAt and accessExpiresAt (+24h)
		- creates/fetches chat room
		- updates room sessionUnlockedAt/sessionExpiresAt
		- auto-sends portfolio snapshot message to chat as:
			- messageType = portfolio_snapshot
			- payload = structured holdings/sector snapshot
	- On failure: marks payment failed.
- Response:
	{
		"message": "Payment verified successfully",
		"status": "paid",
		"paymentId": "...",
		"chatId": "...",
		"accessExpiresAt": "..."
	}

GET /api/payment/advisor/earnings
- Auth: Protected + advisor role required
- Purpose: Advisor earnings dashboard data.
- Behavior:
	- Aggregates total earnings, paid consultations, unique clients.
	- Returns recent paid payments with client details.
- Response:
	{
		"stats": {
			"totalEarnings": 24500,
			"paidConsultations": 18,
			"uniqueClients": 12
		},
		"recentPayments": [
			{
				"amount": 499,
				"currency": "INR",
				"createdAt": "...",
				"user": {
					"name": "Client Name",
					"email": "client@example.com"
				}
			}
		]
	}

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
6) Chat APIs
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

POST /api/chat/create-room
- Auth: Protected + active payment access check for clients
- Purpose: Ensure chat room exists for client-advisor pair.
- Body:
	{
		"advisorId": "<advisorObjectId>"
	}
- Behavior:
	- Only clients can create consultation rooms.
	- Validates advisor exists and has advisor role.
	- Returns existing room if already created.
- Response:
	{
		"chatId": "<chatRoomId>",
		"message": "Chat room ready"
	}

POST /api/chat/send
- Auth: Protected + payment access middleware
- Purpose: Send message to chat.
- Body:
	{
		"chatId": "<chatRoomId>",
		"message": "Hello advisor"
	}
- Behavior:
	- Sender must be participant in chat.
	- Clients are blocked if session expired.
	- Advisors can continue replying.
- Response:
	{
		"message": "Message sent"
	}

GET /api/chat/messages/:chatId
- Auth: Protected
- Purpose: Fetch ordered message history for a chat.
- Behavior:
	- User must be chat participant (client or advisor).
	- Returns full message docs sorted by createdAt asc.
	- Includes sender (name, email, role).
	- Includes messageType and payload fields for rich UI rendering.
- Response:
	[
		{
			"_id": "...",
			"chat": "...",
			"sender": {
				"_id": "...",
				"name": "Client",
				"email": "client@example.com",
				"role": "client"
			},
			"message": "Consultation started: portfolio snapshot shared...",
			"messageType": "portfolio_snapshot",
			"payload": {
				"holdingsCount": 4,
				"totalInvestment": 1174540,
				"totalCurrentValue": 1174540,
				"sectors": [{ "name": "Energy", "allocation": 48 }],
				"holdings": [{ "symbol": "RELIANCE", "weight": 28 }]
			},
			"createdAt": "..."
		}
	]

GET /api/chat/advisor/rooms
- Auth: Protected + advisor role required
- Purpose: Advisor inbox list with last message preview.
- Response:
	{
		"rooms": [
			{
				"chatId": "...",
				"client": {
					"_id": "...",
					"name": "Client",
					"email": "client@example.com"
				},
				"createdAt": "...",
				"lastMessage": {
					"text": "...",
					"senderName": "Client",
					"createdAt": "..."
				}
			}
		]
	}

GET /api/chat/client/rooms
- Auth: Protected + client role required
- Purpose: Client consultation history.
- Response:
	{
		"rooms": [
			{
				"chatId": "...",
				"advisor": {
					"_id": "...",
					"name": "Advisor",
					"email": "advisor@example.com"
				},
				"createdAt": "...",
				"accessExpiresAt": "...",
				"isSessionActive": true,
				"lastMessage": {
					"text": "...",
					"senderName": "Advisor",
					"createdAt": "..."
				}
			}
		]
	}

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
7) Frontend API Usage Notes
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

- Frontend stores:
	- localStorage token key: token
	- localStorage user key: user
- Axios request interceptor injects Authorization header automatically when token exists.
- Chat API client uses /chat base from VITE_API_BASE_URL.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
8) Environment Variables (Backend)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Required for full functionality:
- PORT
- FRONTEND_URL
- MONGO_URI
- JWT_SECRET
- ADMIN_NAME
- ADMIN_EMAIL
- ADMIN_PASSWORD
- MEGALLM_API_KEY
- RAZORPAY_KEY_ID
- RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
9) Key Functional Behaviors Summary
----------------------------------------


----------------------------------------

- Public registration is client-only.
- Advisor onboarding is admin-only.
- Consultation access requires successful payment and is time-bound to 24 hours.
- Payment verification automatically initializes consultation chat context.
- Portfolio snapshot is auto-shared at session start.
- Chat supports typed messages with rich payload (portfolio_snapshot).
- AI analysis is cached per day to control repeated LLM cost.
- Dashboard can rely on latest cached analysis and 24h price refresh metadata.
